text.tspan: Global Hunger Index vs. extreme poverty
The Global Hunger Index measured against the share of the population livingin extreme poverty (living on less than
$1.90 a day at 2011 international prices). The GHI comprises of four key hunger indicators: prevalence of
undernourishment in the total population; childhood wasting; childhood stunting; and child mortality. This calculation
results in GHI scores on a 100-point scale where 0 is the best score (no hunger) and 100 the worst.versus
Share of population living in extreme poverty
Source: World Bank, Global Hunger Index - IFPRI (2018)
